This paper is about improving the accuracy of a dependency parser using loopy belief propagation through structured factors. This is a common technique used in natural language processing (NLP), which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses adjusting model parameters using back-propagation, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions runtime complexity (O(n^3)), which is a common consideration in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions parsing visual data, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV).
